  "text": "Total yeast DNA was prepared in agarose plugs by standard methods. 44 The agarose plugs were incubated overnight at 37 1C with SalI, using the manufacturerrecommended buffer (Roche Applied Science, Mannheim, Germany); 60 U of the enzyme was used per 100 ml plug. Undigested and digested plugs were separated by pulsed-field electrophoresis in a CHEF Mapper apparatus (CHEF-Mapper DRII, Bio-Rad, Bio-Rad Segrate, Italy) under the conditions that separate Saccharomyces cerevisiae chromosomes. The gels were dehydrated, and southern hybridization was carried out with [ 32 ]P-dCTP-labeled pCMV-CFTR4.6. [CITATION_1] ",
